  "chain": [
    {"repo": "sg-evals/django--674eda1c", "path": "django/db/models/query.py", "symbol": "QuerySet._fetch_all"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/django--674eda1c", "path": "django/db/models/query.py", "symbol": "ModelIterable.__iter__"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/django--674eda1c", "path": "django/db/models/sql/query.py", "symbol": "Query.get_compiler"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/django--674eda1c", "path": "django/db/models/sql/compiler.py", "symbol": "SQLCompiler.execute_sql"}
  ],
  "text": "Django implements lazy queryset evaluation through a multi-layer architecture. The QuerySet class in django/db/models/query.py (line 303) represents a lazy database lookup with a result cache initialized to None (line 311). When a QuerySet is iterated (line 396-412 via __iter__ method), it triggers _fetch_all() (line 2093), which creates a ModelIterable instance and iterates through it to populate the cache.\n\nThe lazy SQL compilation happens in two stages. First, the QuerySet maintains a Query object (line 310, from django.db.models.sql.Query) that holds the query definition without executing it. When iteration begins, ModelIterable.__iter__() (line 91-100) calls Query.get_compiler() (django/db/models/sql/query.py, line 364) to create an SQLCompiler instance.\n\nThe SQLCompiler class (django/db/models/sql/compiler.py, line 40) handles the lazy SQL compilation. The as_sql() method (line 763+) builds the SQL string and parameters without executing anything - this is the lazy compilation phase. The actual SQL string is only generated when needed.\n\nThe database query execution happens in SQLCompiler.execute_sql() (line 1601). This method first calls as_sql() to get the SQL string and parameters (line 1618), then obtains a database cursor from the connection (lines 1627-1629). The actual database query is executed at line 1631 with cursor.execute(sql, params). This is where an OperationalError would be raised if the database is unavailable or the connection fails.\n\nThe execution chain is: QuerySet.__iter__() → QuerySet._fetch_all() → ModelIterable.__iter__() → Query.get_compiler() → SQLCompiler.execute_sql() → cursor.execute(). The lazy evaluation is maintained through the _result_cache mechanism - the query is only compiled and executed when the QuerySet is first iterated, accessed for length, or evaluated with __bool__."
}

